  "market_context": "After a bullish structure with higher highs/lows, price broke the prior swing low during New York session, confirming a Change of Character (CHoCH). Analyst waited for London session open to identify bearish confluence zones for short entry.",
  "key_observation": "The analyst identified an inverted fair value gap and an order block as confluence in the premium zone after CHoCH, and required 1-minute timeframe shift confirmation before entering the short.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified prior bullish market structure with swing high and low, then observed break of the key swing low during New York session, confirming CHoCH and bearish shift.",
    "Step 2: Drew Fibonacci from most recent swing low to high to define premium (above 50% retracement) as the trade zone for shorts.",
    "Step 3: Aligned premium zone with two areas of interest: an inverted FVG and an order block, selecting confluence for entry.",
    "Step 4: Waited for price to enter the confluence zone, then switched to 1-minute chart to await bearish shift confirmation (i.e., rejection after bullish probe).",
    "Step 5: Entered short on 1-minute order block with stop loss above the zone’s high, targeting the M15 swing low.",
    "Step 6: Took partial profit at 5R (50% of position), let remainder run to swing low for total 7.1R reward."
  ],
  "outcome": "Partial profit taken at 5R (50% position closed), remaining 50% ran to swing low achieving ~7.1R total; trade executed successfully during New York session volatility.",
  "lessons": "After CHoCH, wait for lower-timeframe confirmation at confluence zones (IFVG + OB); partial profit at 5R improves expectancy without sacrificing full potential—aligns with SMC risk management principles.",
